OUTLIER_MCB — standing routine (Cursor & any AI assistant)

This repo uses OUTLIER_MCB: an assumption-negation + falsification engine for honest invention/discovery.

WHEN THE USER ASKS FOR SOMETHING NEW / NOVEL / INVENT / DISCOVER IN ENGLISH OR ITALIAN, USE THE LIBRARY — always, by default.
QUANDO L'UTENTE CHIEDE QUALCOSA DI NUOVO / ORIGINALE / INVENTATO / SCOPERTO IN INGLESE O ITALIANO, USA LA LIBRERIA.

  python -c "import OUTLIER_MCB as m; print(m.assistant_brief('''<the request>'''))"

For continuous use after the first activation, use the compact per-turn router:

  python -m OUTLIER_MCB route --problem "<the request>" --json

If activate=false, answer normally. If activate=true, follow entrypoint/next_call and report the broken
assumption, world-test/death-gate, claim-ladder status, and novelty_scope.
Se activate=false, rispondi normalmente. Se activate=true, segui entrypoint/next_call e riporta assunzione
rotta, world-test/death-gate, stato della claim ladder e novelty_scope.

Then obey the brief. For the full loop:
  import OUTLIER_MCB as m
  m.explore("<request>", evaluator=<objective>, prior_art_provider=<online>, llm=<model>)   # invention
  m.explore("<claim>", math_claim="x**2+y**2>=2*x*y", math_variables={"x":(-5,5),"y":(-5,5)})  # theorems → z3/lean

RULES (non-negotiable):
1. Never answer a novelty/invention request from memory — run the library first.
2. Break a hidden assumption and name it; breaking none = INSIDE_THE_BOX (not an answer).
3. Settle EXTERNALLY (data / repo tests / z3 / lean) — never self-certify.
4. Report novelty_scope (LOCAL_ONLY / INCOMPLETE_ONLINE_SEARCH / ONLINE_PRIOR_ART_CHECKED).
5. Never say "absolute novelty" / "new theorem" / "never seen" without formal proof + online prior-art + a passing verifier.
6. Math: FORMALLY_PROVED only when z3/lean confirms; no proof => conjecture, not theorem.

The spark is yours; the rigor is the machine's — every candidate must be able to DIE on a world-test.
